	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64393032">The "technological singularity" is metaphor based on  the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singularity_(mathematics)" title="wikipedia.org">mathematical singularity<span class="substr"> </span></a> [wikipedia.org]<blockquote><div><p>a singularity is a point at which a given mathematical object is not defined, or a point where the mathematical object ceases to be well-behaved in some particular way</p></div></blockquote><p>
In physics, when the mathematics describing a system has a singularity it means that the mathematical description is inadequate to describe the real word. It does not mean that some wild magic thing occurs the breaks reality, it means that our understanding is i</p></div>
	</div>

